        OANDA offers built-in retry discounts: <strong>20% off</strong> for accounts up to $50K and <strong>10% off</strong> for $100K and above. Plus, use code <strong>PROPFIRMS</strong> for 20% off all challenge fees.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <!-- TRADING RULES                                                   -->
  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <div class="mb-10">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3">Trading Rules</h3>
    <p class="mb-4">
      OANDA applies the same trading rules across all accounts, with only a few limits changing on the $500K plan. The rules are designed to control downside risk during the evaluation while limiting how much profit you can concentrate in a single day.
    </p>

    <div class="space-y-3 mb-6">
      <div class="rounded-lg bg-slate-50 border border-slate-200 p-4">
        <p class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Daily Profit Cap (Consistency Rule)</p>
        <p>On $5K – $200K accounts, daily profits are capped at <strong>2% per day</strong>. On the $500K account, the limit increases to <strong>5% per day</strong>. If you reach the cap, all open positions are closed automatically and trading is disabled until the next trading day.</p>
        <p class="text-xs text-teal-600 font-semibold mt-1">This rule applies only during the challenge and is removed once you become a Signal Provider.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-lg bg-slate-50 border border-slate-200 p-4">
        <p class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">News Trading Restrictions</p>
        <p>You can't open or manually close trades <strong>2 minutes before or after</strong> high-impact economic news, creating a 4-minute restriction window. Pending orders triggered during this period are cancelled automatically. There is no soft breach — news trading is treated as a forbidden practice and can result in profit removal or account termination.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-lg bg-slate-50 border border-slate-200 p-4">
        <p class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Stop Loss & Holding Trades</p>
        <p>You're <strong>not required</strong> to use a stop loss, and you're allowed to hold trades overnight and over the weekend, as long as you remain within the daily loss and drawdown limits.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-lg bg-slate-50 border border-slate-200 p-4">
        <p class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Inactivity Rule</p>
        <p>You must place at least one trade every <strong>30 calendar days</strong> to keep your challenge account active. Exceeding this limit is a hard breach and results in account closure. On-hold accounts have an extended 180-day window.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-lg bg-slate-50 border border-slate-200 p-4">
        <p class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Account Merging</p>
        <p>If you pass more than one challenge, you can merge accounts only when the settings are identical, and only up to a maximum combined allocation of <strong>$200,000</strong>. Additional passed accounts above that limit are placed on hold.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Verdict -->
  <div class="rounded-xl border-l-4 border-teal-500 bg-teal-50/60 px-5 py-4">
    <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-teal-800 mb-1">Verdict on OANDA's Challenges and Rules</p>
    <p class="text-sm text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
